    <h1>Frameworks and Tools</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p>This page describes the major technologies which are used for th=
e development of SLAMD. Furthermore, reasons for the concrete choices are d=
escribed.<br>It is important that the choices made take into account the fa=
ct that we are building an MVP. Going far beyond that MVP would require ret=
hinking aspects such as hosting, non-functional as well as functional requi=
rements, resources, team size etc.<br>However, we still build our MVP in su=
ch a way, that adaptions can be made in the future easily by using clean de=
sign and architecture. For example, if in the future a generic REST API ins=
tead of an HTML-based web app is wanted, it would amount to basically only =
changing the controller layer.</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"wrapped confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col>
<col>
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">Technology</th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">Motivation</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Flask</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Flask is a lightweight Python web framework w=
ith a huge community. The setup is simple and can be customized easily. Dja=
ngo, which is another popular web framework, is rather heavyweight and more=
 suited for enterprise applications.<br>For the sake of simplicity and as w=
e are developing an open source web app for a restricted community, Flask s=
eems to be an appropriate choice. Further, for the MVP of SLAMD we do not c=
onstruct a generic REST API which is consumed e.g. by some frontend framewo=
rk on the client-side, but we create HTML templates in terms of Jinja2 and =
return them in our controllers (which are modularized using Flask Blueprint=
).</p><p><a href=3D"https://flask.palletsprojects.com/en/2.1.x/" class=3D"e=
xternal-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Welcome to Flask =E2=80=94 Flask Documentati=
on (2.1.x) (palletsprojects.com)</a></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Jinja2</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Jinja2 is the most popular templating engine =
with perfect Flask integration. It provides features such as macros and tem=
plate inheritance allowing for a modularization of the frontend. As there i=
s a large community using Jinja2 there exists a lot of documentation.</p><p=
><a href=3D"https://palletsprojects.com/p/jinja/" class=3D"external-link" r=
el=3D"nofollow">Jinja | The Pallets Projects</a></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">WTForms</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>WTForms allow for a programmati=
c specification of forms in terms of Python classes. This improves structur=
ing and readability of our code base. Furthermore, the framework provides a=
n easy interface for creating server-side validation of the form's inputs. =
Finally, as there is a large community using WTForms, we can rely on exhaus=
tive documentation.</p><p><a href=3D"https://wtforms.readthedocs.io/en/3.0.=
x/" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">WTForms =E2=80=94 WTForms Docu=
mentation (3.0.x)</a></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">Scikit-learn</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>scikit-learn is largely used in=
 data analysis and machine learning. There is a large community and extensi=
ve documentation. It uses a simple generic interface which is easy to learn=
 and use and provides classes for basically any relevant Machine Learning a=
nd Data Analysis Tool.</p><p><a href=3D"https://scikit-learn.org/stable/ind=
ex.html" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">scikit-learn: machine lea=
rning in Python =E2=80=94 scikit-learn 1.1.1 documentation</a></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">Vanilla JS</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>We rely on using Vanilla Javasc=
ript. The manipulation of UI Elements required in SLAMD can be managed prop=
erly with pure Javascript. We further rely on using the Fetch-API when call=
ing the backend as in our opinion it is more user-friendly and easier to re=
ad and write than ajax/jQuery.</p><p><a href=3D"https://developer.mozilla.o=
rg/en-US/docs/Web/javascript" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Java=
Script | MDN (mozilla.org)</a></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">Pytest</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Pytest is a frequently used tes=
ting framework which has all relevant features for a plethora of testing us=
e cases. From simple assertion and mocking up to creating test clients it c=
an cover unit as well as integration testing.</p><p><a href=3D"https://docs=
.pytest.org/en/7.1.x/" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">pytest: hel=
ps you write better programs =E2=80=94 pytest documentation</a></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">Bootstrap</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Bootstrap is a well known CSS f=
ramework which provides a grid framework for responsive layout as well as v=
arious UI Elements such as modals etc. There is extensive documentation. It=
 is simple to integrate it into an app simply by including it in the html h=
ead element.</p><p><a href=3D"https://getbootstrap.com/" class=3D"external-=
link" rel=3D"nofollow">Bootstrap =C2=B7 The most popular HTML, CSS, and JS =
library in the world. (getbootstrap.com)</a></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">Bootstrap Icons</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><span style=3D"color: rgb(33,37=
,41);">Free, high quality, open source icon library with over 1,600 icons. =
We decided to use this website since we can easily copy the icons as &lt;sv=
g&gt; tags into our code. We do not require installing an additional librar=
y for using the icons as with other offers.</span></p><p><span style=3D"col=
or: rgb(33,37,41);"><a href=3D"https://icons.getbootstrap.com/" class=3D"ex=
ternal-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Bootstrap Icons =C2=B7 Official open source S=
VG icon library for Bootstrap (getbootstrap.com)</a></span></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">Cypress</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">Nice Javascript library for writin=
g acceptance test at the level of the UI. It allows to simulate behaviour b=
y automating the interaction with the browser. It makes sure our UI behaves=
 as expected. Further, it can be easily integrated within github: For more =
details, check the documentation: <a href=3D"https://www.cypress.io/" class=
=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Cypress</a></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
